trend_summary: Built-up footprint expanded steadily via infill estates and light-industrial parks, especially south-east and central corridors. Major road interchange upgrades boosted connectivity. While large forest blocks persist, edge woodland shrank and was replaced by housing, schools and sports fields. Tree planting within existing estates slightly offset overall greenery loss.
notable_changes: New clusters of white-roofed commercial/industrial buildings added in the south-east quadrant.
Large clover-leaf interchange in the centre-south visibly widened and received additional ramps.
Several forest patches in the north-east and west were cleared for new housing blocks and roads.
Recreational green strips and sports facilities introduced within older residential estates, indicating internal greening.
